<subsection xml:id="subsec-magnitude-of-a-vector">
    <title>Magnitude of a Vector</title>
    <p>
        The <alert>magnitude</alert> of vector <m>\mathbf{AB}</m> in 
        <xref ref="magnitude-vect-1"/> can be denoted as <m>|\mathbf{AB}|</m>.
        The magnitude of vector <m>\mathbf{AB}</m> represents the distance between
        point <m>\mathbf{A}</m> and point <m>\mathbf{B}</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
        We can represent the components of vector <m>\mathbf{AB}</m> as 
        <m>\begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix}</m>, where 
        <m>x</m> represents the horizontal displacement and <m>y</m> 
        represents the vertical displacement.
    </p>
    <p>
        We calculate the magnitude of vector <m>\mathbf{AB}</m>
        by applying <alert>Pythagorean theorem</alert> as shown below.
    </p>
    <p>
        <me>
            |\mathbf{AB}| =  \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}
        </me>
    </p>
    <figure xml:id="magnitude-vect-1">
        <caption></caption>
        <image width="60%">
            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
            <latex-image>
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                    \draw[gray!30, very thin, step=0.1] (-1,-1) grid (6,6);
                    \draw[step=1cm,black!40,thick] (-1,-1) grid (6,6);
       
                    % Draw x and y axes
                    \draw[- &gt;] (-1,0) -- (5,0) node[right] {$x \, axis$};
                    \draw[- &gt;] (0,-1) -- (0,5) node[above] {$y \, axis$};

                    % Define points
                    \coordinate (A) at (1,1);
                    \coordinate (B) at (4,5);
                    \coordinate (C) at (4,1);

                    % Draw vector
                    \draw[very thick](A)-- (B);
                    \draw[thin,dashed] (A) -- (C) node[midway, below] {\small $x$};
                    \draw[thin,dashed] (C) -- (B) node[midway, right] {\small $y$};

                    % Draw vector
                    \draw [-{Latex[scale=2]}] (1,1) -- (2.8,3.4); 
                    
                    %draw the right angle
                    \tkzMarkRightAngle[draw=black,size=.2](A,C,B);

                    % Labels
                    \node[left] at (A) {$A$};
                    \node[above] at (B) {$B$};
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
        </image>
    </figure>
