    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Determine the magnitude of vector AB as shown in the <xref ref="magnitude-of-vect"/> below
            </p>
            <figure xml:id="magnitude-of-vect">
                <caption></caption>
                <image width="50%">
                    <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    <latex-image label="magnitude-of-vectors">
                        \begin{tikzpicture}
                            \usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta}
                            % Draw x and y axes
                            \draw[-&gt;] (-1,0) -- (5,0) node[right] {$x$};
                            \draw[-&gt;] (0,-1) -- (0,5) node[above] {$y$};

                            % Define points
                            \coordinate (A) at (0,0);
                            \coordinate (B) at (3,4);
                            \coordinate (C) at (3,0);

                            % Draw triangle
                            \draw[very thick](A)-- (B) -- (C) -- cycle;

                            % Draw vector
                            \draw [-{Latex[scale=2]}] (1.49,2) -- (1.55,2.1); 

                            % Right angle marker
                            \draw[very thick](C) ++(-0.3,0) -- ++(0,0.3) -- ++(0.3,0);

                            % Labels
                            \node[left] at (-0.02,0.2) {$A$};
                            \node[right] at (B) {$B$};
                            \node[below] at (C) {$C$};
                            \node[below] at (1.5,0) {$7$};
                            \node[right] at (3,2) {$24$};
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image>
            </figure>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                To find the magnitude of vector AB, we use pythagora's theorem to find the length AB.
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> AB \amp = \sqrt{\text{(AC)}^2 + \text{(CB)}^2 } </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \sqrt{7^2 + 24^2} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \sqrt{49 + 576}</mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \sqrt{625}</mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = 25 </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                Hence, the magnitude of AB represented as <m>|AB|</m> is <m>25.</m>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
